	<text_base_description>Situated in prime Laurel Canyon, this pristinely revived 1920s Spanish gem captures incredible treetop views. Open the vintage wood front door to find yourself in an oasis of old world charm. Ample amounts of natural light bounce off the soaring ceilings illuminating the details of the hardwood floors, arched windows and custom Mission tile. Dual masters allow for ideal living. Additionally, this captivating home features a sizable bonus room which can be the perfect den or home office. The recently renovated kitchen is fit for a chef. There are numerous outdoor nooks for eating and reading throughout the tranquil grounds, a front-facing balcony, and a large magical patio immersed among enveloping trees complete with firepit and bbq. The oversized two car garage is equipped with abundant storage space.  </text_base_description>
